translated: Torsten Valdemar, assistant to the director, Gothenburg, born on February 13, 1900 in Gothenburg. - High school graduate in Gothenburg in 1920, studied natural economy and more at Gothenburg University from 1921 to 1934, language studies at Columbia University in New York from 1931 to 1932. Employed by AB Gibgs Bank in Gothenburg from 1920 to 1930, worked at J. P. Morgan & Co. in New York in 1931 and 1932, then returned to AB Gibgs Bank, treasurer at the head office from 1936, worked at the Stockholm branch from 1936 to 1940, assistant to the director in Gothenburg since 1941, board secretary. Ivar, hospital doctor, Vänersborg, born on June 17, 1898 in Stockholm to Professor and Rector of the Veterinary University John V. and Olga Tilländer. Married in 1927 to Karin Schött. Children: Gösta born in 1929, Margareta born in 1933, Marianne born in 1938. - High school graduate in 1917 and medical candidate in 1922 in Stockholm, medical licentiate in Uppsala in 1928. Assistant doctor at the academic hospital surgical department in 1926, assistant doctor at the Navy hospital in Karlskrona in 1927, assistant doctor at the academic hospital medical department in 1929, at the gynecology-obstetrics department in the same year, at the ear department in Uppsala in the same year, medical doctor there in 1931, assistant doctor and resident in 1931-1936, temporarily assistant doctor at Sahlgrenska Hospital ear department in 1934, assistant doctor there from 1934 to 1936, practicing doctor in Vänersborg since 1937, doctor at Vänersborg hospital ear department in 1938, senior doctor there since 1941. Navy doctor grant recipient from 1927 to 1928, Navy doctor of the second group in the reserve in 1929, in the Medical Corps in 1930 and in the reserve in 1931, of the first group in the reserve in 1939.
